Description: Portable Plan 9 / kencc C compiler, assembler and linker toolchain
 goken9cc is a portable multi-platform C compiler, assembler, and linker
 toolchain as well as a minimalist C library rooted in the work of Ken
 Thompson and the Plan 9 / Inferno operating systems. It is a fork of the
 kencc toolchain that lived in the Go repository circa 2010, itself forked
 from inferno-os and plan9port.
 .
 It can build C programs targeting the 386, amd64, arm, arm64, riscv and
 mips architectures on Linux and macOS hosts, and ships the Plan 9 mk and
 rc build tools needed to drive it.
 .
 Everything is installed under /usr/lib/goken9cc. The install prefix is
 baked into the binaries at build time, so no GOROOT environment
 variable is exported (which would clash with the Go toolchain); the
 shipped /etc/profile.d/goken9cc.sh only appends the host architecture's
 bin directory to PATH on login shells.
